<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-24T17:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-24T17:30:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/3046: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Valencia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-24T18:00:00-04:30">February 24, 1937—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A … C. R …, departmental passport 362,797, deserter from the Spanish
                            Army, has applied to the Consulate for protection and assistance in
                            returning to the United States. He has not been arrested <pb facs="0495" n="483" xml:id="pg_483"/> but may at any moment. He declares he did
                            not take oath of allegiance or other promise. He is in great danger.
                            Please instruct as to protection.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>